class WeatherForecast { 
   private int temperature; 
   private boolean isStormy; 
   public WeatherForecast(int temperature, boolean storm) { 
       this.temperature = temperature; 
       this.isStormy = storm; 
   } 
   public boolean willItRain() { 
       if (this.temperature < 20 && this.isStormy) { 
           return true; 
       } 
       return false; 
   } 
   public void increaseTemperature(int increment) { 
       this.temperature += increment; 
   } 
}",

If the temperature starts over 20 degrees Celsius and the forecast initially does not indicate rain, but after calling 'increaseTemperature' with a negative argument the forecast changes to rain, can we infer the reduced temperature caused the rain?
